<% page = {
	'title' : 'Frontier Apprentice',
	'key': 'Frontier Apprentice'
} %>
<% assets = {
	'css' : ['frontier/apprentice.css'],
	'js' : ['petController.js']
} %>

<div ng-app id="main" class="experiments" ng-controller="PetListCtrl">
  <div class="no-layout">
    <h1 class="with-tasks"><%- i18n('hello_title')%>
	    <!-- Button to trigger modal -->
			<button href="#task-modal" role="button" class="btn-tasks btn btn-primary btn-small" data-toggle="modal"><%- i18n('see_tasks') %></button>
		</h1>
		<hr/>

    <section>
      <h2>Pets:</h2>
      <div class="row">
	    	<article class="pet col-lg-4" ng-repeat="pet in pets">
	      	<p ng-model="pet.name">Name: {{pet.name}}</p>
	      	<p ng-model="pet.breed">Breed: {{pet.breed}}</p>
	      	<button class="btn btn-danger align-right" ng-click="removePet(pet)">Remove</button>
		    </article>
	    </div>

			<h2>Add a new pet:</h2>
	    <div class="jumbotron row">
      	<div class="control-group col-lg-4" for="newPet_name">
	      	<div class="controls">
		      	<input id="newPet_name" ng-model="newPet.name" placeholder="name">
	      	</div>
      	</div>
      	<div class="control-group col-lg-4">
	      	<div class="controls">
		      	<input id="newPet_breed" ng-model="newPet.breed" placeholder="breed">
		      	<button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit" ng-click="addPet(newPet)">Submit</button>
	      	</div>
      	</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="jumbotron">
      <h2>Data from controller route:</h2>
      <p>Person: <%= person.name %>, Title: <%= person.title %>, Weapon of choice: <%= person.weapon %></p>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>

<!-- Modal -->
<div id="task-modal" class="modal fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
	  <div class="modal-content">
		  <div class="modal-header">
		    <button type="button" class="btn close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Ã—</button>
		    <h3 id="myModalLabel">Tasks:</h3>
		  </div>
		  <div class="modal-body">
		    <ul>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Build a simple "Hello World" web app in the Frontier web stack.
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Check the application into your own GitHub repository.  If you allow it to be public, then there is no charge.</li>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Deploy your app outside of your local development environment.</li>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Enhance your application by adding content to your page and learn how to pass data to your EJS page.</li>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Add more pages.  Wire them to different routes and/or separate controllers.</li>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Learn how to configure a different header.  Here is a skeletal header with just the bare bones elements: mylayout.ejs</li>
					<li><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-ok btn btn-small btn-success"></i> Using Angular, create a simple list of items.  You should be able to view the list and add/edit/delete items.</li>
				</ul>
		  </div>
		  <div class="modal-footer">
		    <button class="btn btn-primary" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
		  </div>
	  </div>
  </div>
</div>